On Mon, 8 Oct 2001, cmeanley wrote:

> Er, never say never, last westy I bought had a red ground wire, went to
> charge the battery and had to look twice. My mind said red=positive, my
> subconcious asked why it was on the wrong side of the battery. Lesson here,
> always question what the po might have done.

Amen to that!  Often the parts place will have a red wire that is the
correct length for the ground or a black for the positive.  The electrons
don't care about the color.  I have a black wire on my
positive lead for that reason, with the stock ground braid on the other
side.  I never really thought about it before!

